President Muhammadu Buhari has condoled with the Kano State government and Council of Chiefs over the death of the Emir of Rano, Alhaji Tafida Abubakar Ila II. Buhari, in a statement issued yesterday by his media aide, Garba Shehu, joined the family and Rano Emirate in mourning the royal father. The president implored his family and the emirate to find solace in his good works and ensure that his legacies are carried on. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here Emir of Rano dies hours after hospitalisation, Buhari mourns 90% of people kidnapped in Kano rescued  - Ganduje Buhari condoles with UAE President over brotherâ€™s death